[It would be helpful to obtain further information on the apparent isolation of the virus from foeti/brain tissue during the 2nd phase of the SBV event (starting early December 2011), as apparently stated in the information from the Netherlands. Earlier reports referred to the isolation of the virus from clinically affected cattle (in Germany), prior to December 2011.

Subscribers are referred to the paper
B Hoffmann, M Scheuch, D Hoper et al. Orthobunyavirus in cattle, Europe, 2011. Emerg Infect Dis. 2012; 18(3). Available http://wwwnc.cdc.gov/eid/ahead-of-print/article/18/3/11-1905_article.htm. - Mod.AS]

